# Samarskoye, Khaybullinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Samarskoye (; , Hamar) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Samarsky Selsoviet, Khaybullinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 877 as of 2010. There are 10 streets.
Geography
Samarskoye is located 21&nbsp;km north of Akyar (the district's administrative centre) by road. Buribay is the nearest rural locality.
